<TITLE> Govt to rebuild Sidr-hit schools, colleges </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 28 (bdnews24.com)  The government has decided to rebuild and repair schools and colleges in the cyclone-battered south within a month, a government statement said Wednesday. It also decided to write off form filling fees for the SSC and HSC candidates and give money to the students to buy books. The decisions came from a meeting presided over by education secretary Md Momtazul Islam. The meeting decided to sanction Tk 2 lakh for each totally-destroyed institution, Tk 50,000 for necessary furniture and Tk 50,000 for each partially-damaged institution. Tk 2 lakh will be given to each Upazila Nirbahi Officer (UNO) to buy books for the cyclone- affected students. A team led by the additional secretary will monitor the rehabilitation activities, the statement said. bdne
